This paper discusses the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) on graph-structured data, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), social and information networks (cs.SI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Given that the paper focuses on the transformation of classical network structures to graph CNNs, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG and cs.CV, as these sub-categories deal with the development and application of machine learning algorithms and computer vision techniques, respectively. However, since the paper also discusses the use of graph CNNs in social and information networks and bioinformatic datasets, it could also be categorized under cs.SI and cs.NE. Finally, since the paper proposes new network structures for graph CNNs, it could also be categorized under cs.AI, which deals with the development of intelligent agents and systems.
